{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"820919a8-2da2-4d3a-a46e-5775c08af710","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. **MSTest v3 requires .NET 6+ and .NET Framework 4.6.2+**, but with important caveats:\n\n**Problems with your targets:**\n\n| Target | Issue |\n|--------|-------|\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ **Not supported** by MSTest v3. You must drop it or upgrade to `net6.0`+. |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ **Not supported** by MSTest v3. You must upgrade to `net6.0`+. |\n| `net462` | ✅ Still supported. |\n\n**To migrate**, you'd need to update your `TargetFrameworks` to something like:\n\n```\nnet6.0;net462\n```\n\n(or `net8.0` if you want a current LTS target)\n\n**Other breaking changes in MSTest v3 to watch for:**\n- `[DeploymentItem]` behavior changes\n- Some assert APIs were removed/renamed\n- `TestContext` properties changed\n- Default timeout behavior differs\n\nWould you like me to update the project file for MSTest v3?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0266ad40-6095-445d-85fd-f5ac499bfa12","outputTokens":269,"requestId":"BC43:1129F2:2253483:2619D92:69FAA836"},"id":"64469e24-6408-4f6d-83c4-50071cce4fa7","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:32:30.511Z","parentId":"fa4f4546-9605-44c5-b80b-6d23e6710015"}
